criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Women invited for their first or second mammography (45 or 46 y/o) presenting for
             screening;

          2. Willingness and ability to comply with scheduled visits;

          3. Written informed consent obtained prior to performing any protocol-related procedures.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Pregnancy status;

          2. Personal history of prior breast carcinoma, either invasive or ductal carcinoma in
             situ (DCIS) diagnosis;

          3. Ascertained heredo-familial risk according to the standard family history used in
             screening programs;

          4. Participation in another clinical trial on BC screening;

          5. Inability to provide signed informed consent.
